	(47, 'sarah_duterte_wins_2028', 0.87, 0.92, 'Early opinion polls from Tangere and Manila Times show VP Sara Duterte leading her closest rival by 16 points in 2028 presidential preference, indicating broad support amid her official bid announcement, despite vocal opposition and impeachment discussions.', 'High volume of recent coverage from BBC, Al Jazeera, AP, Inquirer, and Wikipedia updates on her presidential run and leading polls demonstrates national dominance in political discourse.', 0.9, '2026-02-01', 'Consensus slightly increased due to new early polls showing Sara Duterte leading by 16 points, while attention rose with ongoing media coverage of her announcement and poll results compared to yesterday.'),
	(48, 'marcos_robredo_2028', 0.25, 0.55, 'Both Marcos and Robredo insisted the meeting was solely about flood control and infrastructure funding with no political discussion; palace deems endorsement talk ''untimely,'' reinforcing strong skepticism and rejection of the proposition amid historical rivalry.', 'Several major Philippine news outlets like Inquirer, GMA, and ABS-CBN ran stories today on the Naga meeting and related speculation, marking it as a moderate talking point, though X searches yielded no significant posts.', 0.7, '2026-02-02', 'Attention slightly increased due to mainstream news coverage of Marcos'' Naga visit with Robredo sparking 2028 team-up rumors, while consensus held steady amid official denials emphasizing non-political intent.'),
	(49, 'sarah_duterte_wins_2028', 0.84, 0.93, 'Supporters portray Sara Duterte as an underdog whose popularity surges amid attacks, with calls like ''President Sara Duterte 2028''; opposition like Risa Hontiveros claims a united front can defeat her, indicating broad but not unanimous agreement on her frontrunner viability.', 'High volume of recent X posts from news outlets and influencers with thousands of views/engagements, plus international and local news coverage (BBC, AP, Al Jazeera) on her presidential bid announcement and impeachments.', 0.85, '2026-02-02', 'Scores remained largely stable compared to yesterday, with a slight dip in consensus due to fresh impeachment filings and opposition rhetoric, offset by pro-Duterte narratives framing attacks as beneficial to her campaign.'),
