	(101, 'duterte_guilty_icc', 0.42, 0.92, 'Public discourse is polarized with Duterte supporters rejecting guilt by framing speeches as hyperbole, questioning ICC bias and delays, and noting persistent drug-related killings under Marcos Jr.; critics affirm guilt via victim impacts and moral critiques, preventing broad agreement.', 'High volume of recent X posts, viral news clips from major outlets like GMA, ABS-CBN, Philstar, and live hearing coverage dominate Philippine timelines, signaling national-level virality.', 1, '2026-02-26', 'Consensus slightly decreased due to robust defense presentations emphasizing hyperbole, bias, and post-Duterte killings, while attention remained high amid the ongoing ICC confirmation hearings.'),
