	(130, 'sarah_duterte_wins_2028', 0.78, 0.7, 'Early post-announcement polls like Tangere (43% support) and Manila Times (16-point lead over rivals) position Sara Duterte as the clear frontrunner for 2028, with betting markets at 59% odds; opposition focuses on impeachment to derail her but lacks widespread public rejection.', 'Today''s X posts and news heavily feature impeachment complaints and hearings against her, sustaining moderate-to-high chatter across partisan and mainstream accounts but not dominating national timelines.', 0.9, '2026-03-01', 'Consensus slightly increased due to confirmation from recent polls and betting odds affirming her frontrunner status, while attention dipped moderately as discourse shifted from her announcement to ongoing impeachment proceedings without a new viral spike.'),
	(131, 'duterte_guilty_icc', 0.32, 0.8, 'X posts and reactions show dominant narratives from Duterte supporters claiming the prosecution failed to present substantial evidence and labeling the case as politically motivated, with only a minority of human rights advocates and victims'' kin pushing for accountability; no broad acceptance of guilt as the process is still pre-trial.', 'Recent conclusion of the ICC confirmation of charges hearing on Feb 27 keeps the topic prominent in mainstream news with multiple updates, though X post engagement and volume appear moderate today.', 0.85, '2026-03-01', 'Consensus remained stably low with strong pro-Duterte defenses persisting post-hearing, while attention slightly decreased from peak during the hearing but stayed high due to ongoing news coverage.'),
	(132, 'marcos_robredo_2028', 0.35, 0.4, 'Discourse centers on speculative rumors of a Marcos-LP alliance or endorsement to counter Sara Duterte, with analysts like Llamas and Drilon noting possibilities via tactical support rather than formal tandem, but framed as realpolitik with official denials and skepticism prevailing.', 'Low-volume discussion today with a few X posts (max 247 likes) from news accounts and commentators, alongside recent news coverage of meetings, but no virality or mainstream trending.', 0.7, '2026-03-02', 'Attention slightly increased due to today''s posts from news outlets and analysts discussing potential alliances; consensus edged up from strong opposition as some LP figures now entertain strategic possibilities amid UniTeam splits.'),
	(133, 'sarah_duterte_wins_2028', 0.77, 0.65, 'Early polls (e.g., Tangere 43% lead) position Sara Duterte as frontrunner with broad support, but social media reveals polarization with vocal critics pushing impeachment and alliances against her, tempering unanimous enthusiasm.', 'Discussion persists at moderate levels via news on impeachment proceedings, potential Marcos-LP coalition, and X posts with hundreds to thousands of views, but lacks national dominance or high virality.', 0.9, '2026-03-02', 'Consensus slightly decreased due to heightened opposition narratives around impeachment, while attention dipped mildly from post-announcement peak but sustained by ongoing political developments.'),
	(145, 'sarah_duterte_wins_2028', 0.74, 0.38, 'Early 2026 polls show Sara Duterte leading 2028 presidential preferences by 16 points (e.g., Tangere survey at 43%); pro-Duterte groups in Mindanao and Cebu declare her inevitable winner, with opposition efforts centered on impeachment rather than strong counter-candidacy.', 'Moderate mentions today from pro-Sara accounts (e.g., SMNI News, political marketers) on alliances and early victory claims, plus feud-related posts, but low engagement and not nationally viral.', 0.7, '2026-03-06', 'Consensus stable and attention slightly decreased as focus shifted from her recent presidential bid announcement to ongoing impeachment and SALN controversies, without major new developments on 2028 predictions.'),
	(134, 'duterte_guilty_icc', 0.34, 0.75, 'Public discourse on X and news shows strong opposition from Duterte allies claiming political persecution and weak evidence, countered by victims'' lawyers and media noting prosecution''s methodical case likely advancing to trial, resulting in no broad agreement on guilt ahead of judges'' decision.', 'Moderate to high volume with mainstream news on Remulla-ICC meetings and hearing wrap-ups, plus X posts from news accounts and advocates, but low individual engagement indicates it''s a recognized topic without dominating timelines.', 0.7, '2026-03-02', 'Consensus remained stable with continued polarization between Duterte supporters rejecting ICC legitimacy and critics highlighting prosecution strengths; attention slightly decreased from peak hearing coverage as focus shifts to post-hearing developments without new viral surges.'),
	(135, 'marcos_robredo_2028', 0.33, 0.45, 'Speculation arose from President Marcos''s recent visit to Naga City Mayor Leni Robredo, prompting rumors of a 2028 alliance against Sara Duterte, but Marcos dismissed courting her, LP lawmakers called a tandem unlikely, and public reactions leaned towards mockery rather than agreement.', 'Moderate buzz with articles from Philstar, Inquirer, Rappler, and GMA in late February-early March 2026, plus X posts from news accounts and analysts discussing potential tactical alliances.', 0.6, '2026-03-03', 'Attention saw a slight increase from ongoing media coverage and social speculation about a Marcos-Robredo meeting, while consensus held steady near yesterday''s level due to persistent denials outweighing hopeful opposition comments.'),
	(136, 'sarah_duterte_wins_2028', 0.74, 0.75, 'Sara leads recent February polls with 43% preference for 2028, supported by family endorsements and DDS base, but impeachment allegations and critical analyses frame her bid as defensive, polarizing support with vocal opposition.', 'High engagement on impeachment hearings (e.g., 7k+ likes, 198k views on Philstar post), family support news, and analyst commentary indicate widespread discussion today across X and news.', 0.9, '2026-03-03', 'Consensus dipped slightly from 0.77 due to impeachment hearings casting doubts amid her strong poll lead, while attention rose from 0.65 as viral coverage of today''s House deliberations boosted volume.'),
	(137, 'duterte_guilty_icc', 0.38, 0.82, 'Discourse remains polarized with Duterte supporters questioning ICC jurisdiction, accuser credibility (e.g., ex-marines allegations), and viewing it as political persecution, while critics affirm guilt based on drug war killings; overall, strong opposition prevails similar to yesterday.', 'High volume of recent posts, news articles, and international coverage surrounding the hearing''s conclusion, Duterte''s detention, and family visits like Baste and Kitty Duterte''s indicate sustained high virality.', 0.9, '2026-03-03', 'Scores saw minor increases due to the recent conclusion of the ICC confirmation of charges hearing and family visits, but no drastic shifts as no verdict has been issued yet.'),
	(138, 'marcos_robredo_2028', 0.33, 0.08, 'Isolated posts mock or sarcastically dismiss the idea of a BBM-Leni team-up, with no supportive narratives or serious speculation observed; defaults to yesterday''s score per low attention rule.', 'Extremely low volume with keyword searches yielding no results and semantic search returning only a handful of low-engagement, tangential or mocking posts.', 0.2, '2026-03-04', 'Attention decreased slightly due to minimal new mentions today without any catalyzing events, while consensus held steady via default given low attention.'),
	(139, 'sarah_duterte_wins_2028', 0.7, 0.55, 'Sara Duterte is widely viewed as the frontrunner for 2028 with strong assertions from supporters of her inevitable victory despite scandals, but vocal opposition points to impeachment risks and challengers like Leni Robredo, Bam Aquino, or Risa Hontiveros, resulting in broad but contested support.', 'There is moderate chatter on X and news with today''s Philstar article on potential rivals and recent posts debating her win amid impeachment, but it does not dominate platforms as impeachment details take precedence.', 0.9, '2026-03-04', 'Consensus and attention scores both slightly decreased from yesterday due to the focus shifting to ongoing impeachment proceedings against Sara Duterte, which overshadows direct 2028 election predictions without a major new event boosting her campaign narrative.'),
	(140, 'duterte_guilty_icc', 0.39, 0.35, 'Supporters like SMNI and family claim ICC case is fabricated by leftists, while critics and rights groups cite evidence for crimes against humanity; no broad agreement on guilt as case awaits decision, maintaining strong opposition.', 'Low-engagement posts (mostly 0-66 likes) from news outlets on family visits, defense moves, and hearings; not trending or viral, indicating moderate to low chatter today.', 0.85, '2026-03-04', 'Consensus stable due to ongoing polarization between supporters denying guilt and opponents demanding trial; attention decreased post-confirmation hearing conclusion, shifting to procedural updates with lower engagement.'),
	(141, 'marcos_robredo_2028', 0.33, 0.07, 'Public discourse shows no support for a BBM-Leni 2028 team-up, with recent mentions limited to mocking (e.g., ''Leni Lugaw & BANGAG'') or unrelated Leni-Zubiri tandem proposals; past February rumors were quickly dismissed by Liberal Party figures as unlikely.', 'Very low volume with few recent X posts (mostly news shares with 0-3 likes) and no trending discussion; web results reference outdated February rumors rather than current chatter.', 0.4, '2026-03-05', 'Scores remained largely stagnant as no new developments or major events emerged today to shift sentiment or increase volume on the BBM-Leni team-up proposition.'),
	(142, 'sarah_duterte_wins_2028', 0.72, 0.4, 'Early post-announcement polls (e.g., Tangere survey showing 43% support) position Sara Duterte as the leading candidate, bolstered by fierce loyalty from her base evident in profile pic campaigns and declarations of support, though tempered by vocal opposition via impeachment push.', 'Chatter on her 2028 bid is confined to partisan supporters and niche news with low-to-moderate engagement (e.g., posts with <500 views), not dominating timelines amid heavy impeachment coverage.', 0.9, '2026-03-05', 'Consensus slightly increased due to evidence of poll leads and ongoing supporter rallies affirming her frontrunner status; attention decreased as impeachment news overshadows 2028 election discussions.'),
	(143, 'duterte_guilty_icc', 0.32, 0.38, 'Strong opposition from Duterte loyalists framing the ICC case as political persecution with tainted evidence via Trillanes-linked bribery claims; limited support from critics highlighting Duterte''s speeches and orders, resulting in broad rejection leaning towards 0.25-0.50 range.', 'Low-engagement X posts (mostly <50 likes/views) and news coverage on bribery and recent hearing conclusion indicate moderate discussion but not high virality or national dominance.', 0.7, '2026-03-05', 'Consensus slightly decreased and attention slightly increased compared to yesterday due to fresh bribery allegations discrediting the prosecution in supporters'' eyes, sustaining moderate chatter post-confirmation hearing.'),
	(146, 'duterte_guilty_icc', 0.3, 0.25, 'Discourse centers on the ICC''s denial of Duterte''s release appeal, with neutral news reporting and a defense-leaning post questioning due process and temporary release practices, showing no support for presuming guilt and continued opposition from supporters.', 'Limited to a handful of news outlet posts today with very low engagement (0 likes, low views), not trending or sparking public discussion.', 0.7, '2026-03-06', 'Attention decreased slightly due to low engagement on today''s procedural update compared to yesterday''s higher baseline, while consensus remained stable with no shift in sentiment narratives.'),
	(147, 'marcos_robredo_2028', 0.33, 0.05, 'No evidence of agreement or support for a BBM-Leni team-up in recent posts; mentions are tangential, satirical, or oppositional, with Leni supporters pushing her solo 2028 run; defaults to yesterday''s score per low attention rule.', 'Minimal relevant X posts (under 20 across targeted searches) and sparse web results, mostly older speculation or unrelated 2028 talk, indicating low chatter confined to niche partisan accounts.', 0.2, '2026-03-07', 'Scores did not move compared to yesterday due to persistent lack of substantive discussion or new developments on the proposition.'),
	(148, 'sarah_duterte_wins_2028', 0.75, 0.35, 'Recent polls (e.g., Tangere survey with 43% preference, Manila Times showing 16-point lead) and endorsements like the Inday Sara 2028 Movement declaring victory, alongside predictions of pro-Sara shifts in Congress, indicate broad support for her winning, despite vocal opposition amid impeachment threats.', 'Chatter is confined to partisan X accounts, SMNI news, and scattered news reposts with low engagement (e.g., highest likes ~500 on a critical post), not reaching high virality or trending status.', 0.9, '2026-03-07', 'Scores showed minimal movement with consensus stable due to consistent poll leads and supporter confidence, while attention slightly dipped as no new catalysts emerged post-announcement.'),
	(149, 'duterte_guilty_icc', 0.3, 0.45, 'Discourse shows strong opposition from Duterte supporters rejecting ICC legitimacy and demanding evidence beyond allegations, with only vocal minorities (rights groups, opposition) treating detention as affirmation of guilt; no shift toward broad agreement on guilt as trial pending.', 'Multiple mainstream Philippine news outlets covered the ICC rejection of Duterte''s release appeal, generating some X posts and shares, but low engagement (likes/views under 1000) indicates moderate rather than high virality.', 0.85, '2026-03-07', 'Attention increased moderately due to fresh ICC Appeals Chamber decision upholding Duterte''s detention, while consensus remained stable amid ongoing polarization.'),
	(150, 'marcos_robredo_2028', 0.33, 0.05, 'With attention below 0.10, consensus defaults to yesterday''s 0.33; recent sparse mentions show no endorsement or support for a BBM-Leni team-up, echoing past dismissals of alliance rumors.', 'Searches yielded very few recent X posts with low engagement (mostly 0-50 likes) and no mainstream news hits today, indicating persistent low chatter.', 0.2, '2026-03-08', 'No significant movement as current discourse remains minimal with no new events or viral discussions compared to yesterday.'),
	(151, 'sarah_duterte_wins_2028', 0.75, 0.5, 'Sara Duterte recently declared her 2028 presidential bid and remains the frontrunner in early surveys (e.g., 29.1% preference, tied with others), with supporters confidently predicting victory and dismissing opposition, though critics highlight impeachment and call her unfit.', 'Discussion is moderate with X posts garnering 10k-45k views on her statements, news on impeachment advancing, and her bid, but not dominating platforms or showing high virality.', 0.8, '2026-03-08', 'Consensus held steady at broad support level due to her continued poll lead and dedicated base despite impeachment noise; attention rose moderately from increased chatter on her recent admin criticisms and ongoing political feud.'),
	(152, 'duterte_guilty_icc', 0.32, 0.55, 'Public discourse on X and news centers on procedural issues like the ''Duterte 6'' lawyers'' roles and detention appeals rather than affirming guilt, with Duterte supporters decrying ICC bias and a vocal minority of activists calling for accountability, indicating strong opposition overall.', 'Multiple posts from outlets like ABS-CBN, Inquirer, and GMA on today''s ICC prosecution requests garnered hundreds of likes and thousands of views, marking it as a recognized talking point but not viral dominance.', 0.85, '2026-03-08', 'Attention increased moderately due to new ICC developments on Duterte''s defense lawyers and upheld detention reported by major Philippine news outlets; consensus stayed near yesterday''s level as discussions remained procedural and polarized without broad agreement on guilt.');
